40 SECTION 2.
41 (a) Those members of the Board of Commissioners of Banks County who are serving as
42 such on the effective date of this Act and any person selected to fill a vacancy in any such
43 office shall continue to serve as such members until the regular expiration of their respective
44 terms of office and upon the election and qualification of their respective successors.
45 (b) Commissioner Districts 1, 2, 3, and 4, as they exist immediately prior to the effective
46 date of this Act, shall continue to be designated as Commissioner Districts 1, 2, 3, and 4,
47 respectively, but as newly described under this Act, and on and after the effective date of this
48 Act, such members of the board serving from those former commissioner districts shall be
49 deemed to be serving from and representing their respective districts as newly described
50 under this Act.
51 SECTION 3.
52 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
53 without such approval.
54 SECTION 4.
55 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
